NAME
	net-gauge (display) - render tcp/udp connection-count headlines from a two-line census file and a sparkline of the tcp column from a history file

INTERFACE
	display (MatrixDisplay)

READS
	net/current	two lines, keyed on first token:
			tcp total connected announced
			udp total connected announced
	net/history	one line per sample: ts tcp_total tcp_conn udp_total,
			oldest first (only tcp_total is plotted)

MOUNT
	The outdir of a service that produces net/current and net/history
	- /tmp/matrix/<service>.  With sysmon-svc: /tmp/matrix/sysmon-svc.
	Include that service in the same composition (e.g.
	`service sysmon-svc /`) so its outdir is populated.

WRITES
	none (renders only)

DESCRIPTION
	Headlines the tcp and udp census counts and plots tcp_total as a
	right-aligned bar sparkline auto-scaled to the history peak (peak
	readout top right).  Re-reads on every update tick.  No pointer
	or key handling.

SEE ALSO
	sysmon-svc (produces net/current and net/history in its outdir)
